
摘  要
在很多重要的生物过程中，蛋白质-RNA相互作用都起到了非常重要的作用，如mRNA的合成、转录、翻译、核糖体的组装。而蛋白质-RNA相互作用的产生则依赖于结合蛋白的结合位点，所以对于RNA结合蛋白的预测研究对定点突变和功能注释有着非常重要的意义，对于理解蛋白质-RNA之间的相互作用机制同样具有非常重要的意义。
为了达到研究目的，使用了氨基酸的位置特异性评分矩阵（PSSM）作为特征输入，数据集采用RBP109数据集，将氨基酸序列使用PSI-BLAST在非冗余蛋白质库nr上进行序列比对得到PSSM，然后在Spark分布式平台上采用MLlib库，对蛋白质-RNA相互作用位点进行了预测。在预测过程中，分别交叉研究了数据的平衡、数据标准化和五折交叉验证对模型预测的影响，还测试了MLlib库中提供的三种机器学习算法，分别为支持向量机（SVM）、逻辑回归（Logistic Regression）和决策树（Decision Tree）。模型的评估则分别使用AUC、准确率（ACC）、马修斯相关性系数(MCC)、精确率（P）、召回率（R）来评估，然后对模型的评估指标AUC值进行排序，得到最优模型的参数。在总共的最优模型训练中，一共训练了97个最优模型，得到最高的AUC值为0.69，其模型参数为：未进行数据平衡，进行数据标准化，进行五折交叉验证，逻辑回归算法，迭代次数100 ，步长1.0，正则化参数0.01。
关键词：大数据处理；机器学习；蛋白质-RNA；结合位点；Spark
 
 
Abstract
In many important biological processes, protein-RNA interactions play a very important role, such as mRNA synthesis, transcription, translation, and ribosome assembly. The production of protein-RNA interactions depends on the binding site of the binding protein. Therefore, the prediction studies of RNA-binding proteins are of great significance for site-directed mutagenesis and functional annotation, and the same mechanism for understanding protein-RNA interactions It is of great significance.
In order to achieve the purpose of the study, the amino acid position-specificity scoring matrix (PSSM) was used as the feature input. The data set was the RBP109 data set. The sequence alignment of the amino acid sequence was performed using PSI-BLAST on non-redundant protein library nr to obtain PSSM. The MLlib library was then used on the Spark distributed platform to predict protein-RNA interaction sites. During the forecasting process, the effects of data balance, data standardization, and five-fold cross validation on model predictions were studied separately. The three machine learning algorithms provided in the MLlib library were also tested. They were support vector machines (SVM) and logic. Logistic Regression and Decision Tree. The assessment of the model was evaluated using AUC, Accuracy (ACC), Matthews Correlation Coefficient (MCC), Precision (P), and Recall (R), respectively, and then the model's evaluation index AUC value was ranked. The optimal model parameters. In the total optimal model training, a total of 97 optimal models were trained to obtain the highest AUC value of 0.69, it’s parameters: no data balance, data standardization, five-fold cross validation, logistic regression algorithm, number of iterations 100, step size 1.0, regularization parameter 0.01.

Key Words：Big data processing; Machine learning; Protein-RNA; Binding site; Spark
 

